        <p><strong>Where Koala wins:</strong> Amazon affiliate workflows and the absolute cheapest entry into one-shot SEO article generation. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if you want articles that rank without managing word credits and editor workload. Pick by the job, not the brand.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Koala AI?</h2>
        <p>Koala AI is a low-cost AI writing platform launched in 2023, built around two complementary tools — <strong>KoalaWriter</strong> (one-shot SEO article generation) and <strong>KoalaChat</strong> (a ChatGPT-style interface tuned for marketing tasks). The product is positioned squarely at solo creators, Amazon affiliates, and budget-conscious niche site builders.</p>

        <p>The core suite does five things:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>KoalaWriter</strong> — paste a keyword, get a 1,500–3,000 word SEO article in 60 seconds</li>
          <li><strong>KoalaChat</strong> — ChatGPT-style chat tuned for marketing workflows</li>
          <li><strong>Amazon Mode</strong> — pulls product data and generates affiliate reviews</li>
          <li><strong>WordPress integration</strong> — direct publishing with featured images</li>
          <li><strong>Bulk Mode (Pro)</strong> — queue keywords for batch article generation</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Koala is <em>not</em>: a brand voice platform, an enterprise tool, or a managed service. It's an engine. Editorial quality and workflow are on you.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>Koala AI is a small bootstrapped team operating remotely. Founded by Jack Tinz, the product gained traction in the Amazon affiliate community before expanding to general SEO workflows. No public funding. Customer base skews heavily toward solo niche site builders and small agencies.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Koala AI features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is focused on speed and price. Here's what actually matters in daily use.</p>

        <h3>1. KoalaWriter — one-shot SEO article generation</h3>
        <p>The flagship. Paste a keyword. Pick an article type (informational, product review, comparison, listicle). Hit generate. 60 seconds later, a full 1,500–3,000 word article appears — with H2/H3 structure, intro, body, FAQ, conclusion, and optional images. Output quality is competent on standard briefs. Complex or technical topics need heavier editing.</p>

        <h3>2. KoalaChat — marketing chat interface</h3>
        <p>Like ChatGPT, but pre-tuned for SEO and marketing tasks. Quick prompts for keyword ideation, meta description rewrites, content briefs, and content audits. Less impressive than dedicated chat models — most users default to ChatGPT or Claude for chat tasks.</p>

        <h3>3. Amazon Mode — affiliate article generator</h3>
        <p>The most differentiated feature in the product. Paste an Amazon URL or ASIN, and Koala pulls product specifications, reviews, ratings, and pricing — then generates a structured product review or comparison article with affiliate links pre-inserted. Genuinely useful for Amazon affiliate site builders.</p>

        <h3>4. WordPress integration</h3>
        <p>Native WordPress plugin. Push articles directly to your CMS with featured images, categories, tags, and SEO meta fields. Reliable for solo publishers; lacks the workflow polish of enterprise tools.</p>

        <h3>5. Bulk Mode (Pro + Business)</h3>
        <p>Queue 50+ keywords and Koala generates articles for each in batch. Useful for niche site builders covering long-tail clusters. <strong>Same caveat as Junia:</strong> bulk output requires editorial review before publishing — Google's Helpful Content updates have targeted unsupervised bulk AI content specifically.</p>

        <h3>6. SEO scoring</h3>
        <p>Built-in keyword optimization scoring. Lighter than Surfer SEO. Sufficient for solo workflows where ranking signals are coming from topical authority rather than pure on-page optimization.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Koala AI pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>Koala publishes pricing. Here are the live numbers — and the word credit reality check.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
