            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>Annual billing saves about 20%. Business tier includes 5 user seats. The word counter includes both KoalaWriter output and KoalaChat conversations — both burn the same pool.</p>

        <h3>The word credit reality</h3>
        <p>The Essentials $9/mo plan markets "150,000 words" like it's a lot. In practice:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>One 2,500-word KoalaWriter article = ~3,000 credits (output + system prompts)</li>
          <li>150,000 words ≈ 50 short articles or 15–20 long-form pieces</li>
          <li>KoalaChat conversations consume credits separately</li>
          <li>Regenerations and edits burn additional credits</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Real-world: most active users blow through Essentials in week two and upgrade to Starter ($25/mo). Pro ($49/mo) is required once you're publishing 30+ articles monthly with regenerations.</p>

