        <h2 id="verdict">Is Koala AI worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For Amazon affiliate site builders: yes.</strong> Amazon Mode is genuinely the best-in-class feature for this workflow. Pro ($49/mo annual) is the right tier. Combine with editorial review and you have one of the most cost-effective stacks for niche affiliate sites.</p>

        <p><strong>For solo creators publishing under 20 articles/month: yes, on Starter ($25/mo).</strong> Skip Essentials — you'll burn through credits in week two. Starter gives you GPT-5 access and enough words for a serious solo workflow.</p>

        <p><strong>For SMBs and brand-sensitive teams: probably no.</strong> No brand voice training, lighter SEO scoring, and a customer base heavily skewed toward affiliates. Mid-market AI writers (Writesonic, Copy.ai) or done-for-you services fit better.</p>

